1
00:00:03,123 --> 00:00:06,456
-ONCE UPON A TIME,
MANY YEARS AGO,

2
00:00:06,456 --> 00:00:09,190
THERE WAS A HAPPY PRINCE.

3
00:00:10,990 --> 00:00:13,890
HE RECALLED NO PAINFUL PAST

4
00:00:13,890 --> 00:00:17,090
AND KNEW NO PAINFUL FUTURE.

5
00:00:18,690 --> 00:00:24,256
ONE DAY, THE PRINCE
OBTAINED A COMFORTING WARMTH.

6
00:00:24,256 --> 00:00:27,256
THE SOURCE OF THIS WARMTH,
HOWEVER,

7
00:00:27,256 --> 00:00:30,990
EMANATED NOT ONLY TRANQUILITY

8
00:00:30,990 --> 00:00:37,423
BUT ALSO UNHAPPINESS, PAIN,
AND LONELINESS.

9
00:00:40,756 --> 00:00:43,556
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

10
00:00:54,590 --> 00:00:57,456
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

11
00:01:23,323 --> 00:01:26,123
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

12
00:02:08,356 --> 00:02:11,723
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "FINAL
WALTZ AND APOTHEOSIS" FROM
"THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

13
00:02:29,919 --> 00:02:32,219
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

14
00:02:34,753 --> 00:02:37,186
[ SLOW FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

15
00:02:41,386 --> 00:02:43,186
-WHAT ARE YOU READING?

16
00:02:43,186 --> 00:02:44,186
-NOTHING.

17
00:02:44,186 --> 00:02:46,053
IT'S NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

18
00:02:46,053 --> 00:02:48,353
-"THE PRINCE AND THE RAVEN,"
HUH?

19
00:02:48,353 --> 00:02:50,286
I SEE.
-WHAT?

20
00:02:50,286 --> 00:02:52,419
-SEEMS
YOU'VE GAINED AN INTEREST

21
00:02:52,419 --> 00:02:54,919
IN SEEING MYTHO
AS HE WAS IN THE STORY,

22
00:02:54,919 --> 00:02:57,586
BACK BEFORE HE LOST HIS HEART.

23
00:02:57,586 --> 00:03:00,219
-ARE YOU IMPLYING I'M THE ONE
RESTORING MYTHO'S HEART?

24
00:03:00,219 --> 00:03:02,419
-AM I WRONG, THEN?

25
00:03:02,419 --> 00:03:03,419
HOLD IT.

26
00:03:03,419 --> 00:03:05,586
-[ GASPS ]

27
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:08,953
[ CHUCKLES ]
-WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

28
00:03:08,953 --> 00:03:12,319
-WHAT WOULD YOU DO
IF PRINCESS TUTU REALLY EXISTED?

29
00:03:12,319 --> 00:03:13,953
-DID SOMETHING HAPPEN?

30
00:03:13,953 --> 00:03:16,119
-NO, NOTHING HAPPENED.

31
00:03:16,119 --> 00:03:18,186
[ CHUCKLES ]

32
00:03:22,953 --> 00:03:25,286
[ MID-TEMPO PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]
-YES, THAT'S RIGHT.

33
00:03:25,286 --> 00:03:27,119
ELONGATE YOUR SPINE.

34
00:03:27,119 --> 00:03:28,753
-HEY, DUCK,
MADE UP YOUR MIND YET?

35
00:03:28,753 --> 00:03:29,986
-ABOUT WHAT?

36
00:03:29,986 --> 00:03:31,119
[ BOTH GASP ]
WHAT?

37
00:03:31,119 --> 00:03:33,186
-DID YOU FORGET
WHAT'S GOING ON TODAY?

38
00:03:33,186 --> 00:03:34,619
-UM, I GUESS I DID.

39
00:03:34,619 --> 00:03:36,186
-[ GASPS ]
-HUH?

40
00:03:36,186 --> 00:03:37,886
-THE FIRE FESTIVAL.

41
00:03:37,886 --> 00:03:39,553
-THE WHAT, NOW?
-DON'T YOU REMEMBER?

42
00:03:39,553 --> 00:03:42,453
WE'RE ASKING IF YOU'VE
DECIDED WHAT YOU'RE GONNA
WEAR TO THE FESTIVAL.

43
00:03:42,453 --> 00:03:44,919
-SO, WHAT'S
THIS FIRE FESTIVAL AGAIN?

44
00:03:44,919 --> 00:03:46,986
-OH, IT'S OKAY, DUCK! IT'S OKAY!

45
00:03:46,986 --> 00:03:49,586
EVEN IF YOU LACK ANY COMMON
SENSE LIVING IN THIS TOWN

46
00:03:49,586 --> 00:03:51,353
AND NOT KNOWING ABOUT
THE FIRE FESTIVAL,

47
00:03:51,353 --> 00:03:53,119
YOU'RE JUST SO DARN CUTE!

48
00:03:53,119 --> 00:03:55,386
-[ Thinking ] <i>BECAUSE</i>
<i>I'M JUST A BIRD TO BEGIN WITH.</i>

49
00:03:55,386 --> 00:03:57,853
-MISS DUCK.
<i>-YEAH, YEAH. SO, I'M A DUCK.</i>

50
00:03:57,853 --> 00:03:59,686
-MISS DUCK!
<i>-I KNOW, ALREADY!</i>

51
00:03:59,686 --> 00:04:01,219
-MISS DUCK!

52
00:04:01,219 --> 00:04:04,253
-I GET IT!
TELL ME ABOUT THE FIRE FESTIVAL!

53
00:04:04,253 --> 00:04:05,386
OOH!

54
00:04:05,386 --> 00:04:07,253
-VERY WELL.

55
00:04:07,253 --> 00:04:09,019
I'LL TELL YOU.
-Y-YES, SIR.

56
00:04:09,019 --> 00:04:11,086
-THE FIRE FESTIVAL
IS A TOWN FÃªTE

57
00:04:11,086 --> 00:04:14,053
WHERE FOLKS DRESS IN
THE OLD WAYS AND DANCE
'ROUND A BONFIRE.

58
00:04:14,053 --> 00:04:16,553
-I SEE, THEN.
I THINK I UNDERSTAND IT NOW.

59
00:04:16,553 --> 00:04:18,586
-BUT MOST IMPORTANT OF ALL

60
00:04:18,586 --> 00:04:20,486
IS THE GOLDEN APPLE
GIVEN TO THE COUPLE

61
00:04:20,486 --> 00:04:23,886
WHO DANCES THE MOST EXQUISITELY
AT THE EVENT.

62
00:04:23,886 --> 00:04:26,353
-GOLDEN APPLE?
-THAT'S RIGHT.

63
00:04:26,353 --> 00:04:29,019
IT'S SAID THAT THE COUPLE TO
WHOM THE GOLDEN APPLE IS GIVEN

64
00:04:29,019 --> 00:04:30,719
WILL BE BOUND TOGETHER FOREVER.

65
00:04:30,719 --> 00:04:33,086
<i>-BOUND TOGETHER FOREVER?</i>

66
00:04:33,086 --> 00:04:34,919
<i>BUT THAT'S</i>
<i>NOTHING TO DO WITH ME.</i>

67
00:04:34,919 --> 00:04:37,153
-MISS DUCK.
<i>-RIGHT, BECAUSE I'M A DUCK.</i>

68
00:04:37,153 --> 00:04:39,553
-MISS DUCK!
<i>-BUT THAT'S OKAY. I KNOW IT!</i>

69
00:04:39,553 --> 00:04:42,586
-MISS DUCK!!
-I SAID I KNOW THA--

70
00:04:42,586 --> 00:04:43,519
OH.

71
00:04:43,519 --> 00:04:44,986
I'M SO SORRY.

72
00:04:44,986 --> 00:04:47,986
-[ YOWLS, HISSES ]

73
00:04:47,986 --> 00:04:50,353
AS PUNISHMENT
FOR YOUR LACK OF FOCUS,

74
00:04:50,353 --> 00:04:52,286
YOU WILL CLEAN THE
ADVANCED CLASS'S LESSON ROOM.

75
00:04:52,286 --> 00:04:54,186
IF YOU DON'T DO IT PROPERLY...

76
00:04:54,186 --> 00:04:56,186
I WILL HAVE YOU MARRY ME!

77
00:04:56,186 --> 00:04:58,353
[ YOWLING ]
-[ WHINES ]

78
00:04:58,353 --> 00:05:00,719
-BE A GOOD GIRL
AND CLEAN THE ROOM.

79
00:05:00,719 --> 00:05:02,919
-YES, 'CAUSE IF YOU
WIN THE APPLE BY SOME FLUKE,

80
00:05:02,919 --> 00:05:04,886
YOU'LL BE BOUND.

81
00:05:06,986 --> 00:05:08,053
-MYTHO.

82
00:05:09,553 --> 00:05:11,086
MYTHO.

83
00:05:12,886 --> 00:05:15,486
I TOLD HIM NOT TO LEAVE
WITHOUT ASKING.

84
00:05:15,486 --> 00:05:18,253
-[ SIGHS ]
THE GOLDEN APPLE, HUH?

85
00:05:20,019 --> 00:05:21,886
-TRY NOT TO FORGET, NOW.

86
00:05:21,886 --> 00:05:23,719
THE PRINCESS
WHO SAVES THE PRINCE

87
00:05:23,719 --> 00:05:27,219
IS FATED NEVER
TO BE WITH HER DEARLY BELOVED.

88
00:05:27,219 --> 00:05:29,986
-[ GRUMBLES ] I DON'T CARE.

89
00:05:32,853 --> 00:05:34,319
HMM?

90
00:05:36,353 --> 00:05:38,086
[ GASPS ] OH!

91
00:05:39,653 --> 00:05:40,819
AAH!

92
00:05:43,186 --> 00:05:45,353
MYTHO?

93
00:05:45,353 --> 00:05:47,819
<i>HE'S A PRINCE.</i>

94
00:05:47,819 --> 00:05:49,753
<i>IS THIS THE REAL YOU, MYTHO?</i>

95
00:05:49,753 --> 00:05:51,919
-TRY NOT TO FORGET, NOW --

96
00:05:51,919 --> 00:05:53,886
SOON AS YOU CONFESS YOUR LOVE,

97
00:05:53,886 --> 00:05:58,119
YOU'LL TURN INTO
A SPECK OF LIGHT AND VANISH.

98
00:05:58,119 --> 00:06:00,853
-UH, UH, THAT IS,
I'M ON CLEANING DUTY

99
00:06:00,853 --> 00:06:02,719
AS PUNISHMENT,
SO, PLEASE, DON'T MIND ME.

100
00:06:02,719 --> 00:06:04,786
-HAVE YOU SEEN RUE ANYWHERE?

101
00:06:04,786 --> 00:06:06,786
-HUH?

102
00:06:06,786 --> 00:06:08,619
UH...

103
00:06:08,619 --> 00:06:10,586
SEEN RUE?

104
00:06:10,586 --> 00:06:14,553
-RUE SAID SHE WANTED TO PRACTICE
DANCING FOR THE FIRE FESTIVAL,

105
00:06:14,553 --> 00:06:16,786
SO I'VE BEEN
WAITING HERE ALL DAY.

106
00:06:16,786 --> 00:06:18,186
<i>-OH.</i>

107
00:06:18,186 --> 00:06:20,686
<i>SO MYTHO'S GOING TO BE</i>
<i>DANCING WITH RUE TONIGHT.</i>

108
00:06:20,686 --> 00:06:24,019
<i>OF COURSE.</i>
-WHEN I'M ALONE...

109
00:06:24,019 --> 00:06:25,353
-[ GASPS ]

110
00:06:25,353 --> 00:06:28,619
-...IT FEELS SO DARK AND COLD.

111
00:06:28,619 --> 00:06:29,953
-FEELINGS?

112
00:06:29,953 --> 00:06:31,786
-WILL YOU BE GOING TONIGHT,
DUCK?

113
00:06:31,786 --> 00:06:32,653
-OH...

114
00:06:32,653 --> 00:06:36,386
HE JUST CALLED ME BY NAME.

115
00:06:36,386 --> 00:06:37,453
[ GASPS ]

116
00:06:39,886 --> 00:06:41,319
AHHH.

117
00:06:41,319 --> 00:06:43,386
[ TWINKLE! TWINKLE! ]

118
00:06:43,386 --> 00:06:45,586
-COME, DUCK. LET'S DANCE.

119
00:06:45,586 --> 00:06:48,019
-[ GASPS ] MYTHO! AAH!

120
00:06:48,019 --> 00:06:49,953
I CAN'T GO TO THE FIRE FESTIVAL.

121
00:06:49,953 --> 00:06:51,986
HUH?!

122
00:06:51,986 --> 00:06:54,419
<i>MYTHO WANTED --</i>

123
00:06:54,419 --> 00:06:57,986
<i>MYTHO WANTED TO DANCE</i>
<i>OF HIS OWN WILL!</i>

124
00:06:57,986 --> 00:07:02,019
<i>COULD IT BE BECAUSE</i>
<i>HE'S REGAINING HIS HEART?</i>

125
00:07:02,019 --> 00:07:05,053
<i>IF IT IS, I'D BE HAPPY.</i>

126
00:07:05,053 --> 00:07:07,719
[ MID-TEMPO
CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

127
00:07:11,119 --> 00:07:13,586
-UH...

128
00:07:13,586 --> 00:07:15,553
[ STAMMERS ]

129
00:07:20,619 --> 00:07:22,953
-HER AGAIN.

130
00:07:22,953 --> 00:07:24,953
DAMN.

131
00:07:24,953 --> 00:07:27,619
-[ GASPS ] PLEASE, EXCUSE ME.

132
00:07:27,619 --> 00:07:28,819
UNH.

133
00:07:30,853 --> 00:07:33,319
[ <i>CHUCKLES</i> ]
<i>I CAN'T BELIEVE IT!</i>

134
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:35,686
<i>I DANCED WITH MYTHO THE PRINCE!</i>

135
00:07:35,686 --> 00:07:38,853
[ LAUGHS ]

136
00:07:38,853 --> 00:07:41,553
-HAVE YOU SEEN RUE ANYWHERE?

137
00:07:43,219 --> 00:07:46,486
<i>-BUT THAT WAS IN RUE'S PLACE.</i>

138
00:07:46,486 --> 00:07:47,986
[ SIGHS ]

139
00:07:47,986 --> 00:07:49,486
-HUH?

140
00:07:49,486 --> 00:07:51,986
-[ GROANING ]

141
00:07:51,986 --> 00:07:53,953
-SHE PRACTICALLY IS A DUCK.

142
00:07:56,053 --> 00:07:57,353
-CLEANING! OH!

143
00:07:57,353 --> 00:07:58,453
-HEY!

144
00:08:00,819 --> 00:08:02,353
[ GROANS ]

145
00:08:02,753 --> 00:08:06,153
-[ GRUNTS ]
THAT VOICE JUST NOW.

146
00:08:06,153 --> 00:08:08,453
OHH.
[ DOOR OPENS ]

147
00:08:08,986 --> 00:08:11,053
I KNEW IT WAS HIM.
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

148
00:08:11,053 --> 00:08:13,053
UH...

149
00:08:13,053 --> 00:08:14,719
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK,
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK.

150
00:08:14,719 --> 00:08:16,019
-[ Muffled ]
WHAT'S THE MEANING OF THIS?

151
00:08:16,019 --> 00:08:17,986
-QUACK?! QUACK?

152
00:08:17,986 --> 00:08:20,353
-DRESSED IN THIS SILLY OUTFIT.

153
00:08:20,353 --> 00:08:22,219
-RUE SAID TO WEAR IT.

154
00:08:22,219 --> 00:08:25,186
-LISTEN, ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS OBEY MY ORDERS

155
00:08:25,186 --> 00:08:28,153
AND DON'T PAY ANY HEED
TO WHAT ANYONE ELSE TELLS YOU.

156
00:08:28,153 --> 00:08:30,653
THAT INCLUDES WHAT RUE SAYS.

157
00:08:30,653 --> 00:08:32,453
SO, YOU WERE DANCING?

158
00:08:32,453 --> 00:08:33,986
-YES.

159
00:08:33,986 --> 00:08:35,686
-WHAT'S WITH THAT DUCKLIKE GIRL

160
00:08:35,686 --> 00:08:37,886
THAT I'VE SEEN
SCURRYING AROUND LATELY?

161
00:08:37,886 --> 00:08:39,819
<i>-DUCKLIKE?</i>

162
00:08:39,819 --> 00:08:42,053
<i>WELL, I AM A DUCK, BUT --</i>

163
00:08:42,053 --> 00:08:44,453
-SHE'S CALLED "DUCK."
HER NAME IS DUCK.

164
00:08:44,453 --> 00:08:46,386
-I DIDN'T ASK FOR TRIVIA.
-QUACK.

165
00:08:46,386 --> 00:08:48,486
-THERE'S NO NEED TO DANCE
WITH THE LIKES OF HER

166
00:08:48,486 --> 00:08:50,286
JUST BECAUSE SHE ASKED.

167
00:08:50,286 --> 00:08:52,686
-THAT'S NOT WHAT HAPPENED.

168
00:08:52,686 --> 00:08:56,919
RUE HADN'T COME,
AND I'D BEEN WAITING BY MYSELF.

169
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:59,419
THEN DUCK CAME, SO...

170
00:08:59,419 --> 00:09:02,819
-ARE YOU SAYING
YOU INVITED HER TO DANCE?

171
00:09:02,819 --> 00:09:04,786
-YES.

172
00:09:04,786 --> 00:09:06,619
-DON'T MAKE ME REPEAT MYSELF.

173
00:09:06,619 --> 00:09:09,053
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS LISTEN TO WHAT I TELL YOU

174
00:09:09,053 --> 00:09:11,686
AND STOP WASTING YOUR TIME
ON SUCH USELESS NONSENSE.

175
00:09:11,686 --> 00:09:13,686
-[ <i>GRUNTS</i> ] <i>I CAN'T HEAR.</i>

176
00:09:13,686 --> 00:09:15,386
-WHEN YOU WERE
WANDERING AIMLESSLY,

177
00:09:15,386 --> 00:09:17,386
COMPLETELY STRIPPED
OF ALL YOUR MEMORIES,

178
00:09:17,386 --> 00:09:19,586
I WAS THE ONE
WHO GAVE YOU THE NAME OF MYTHO.

179
00:09:19,586 --> 00:09:23,019
I'M THE ONE WHO SAVED YOU,
AND DON'T EVER FORGET THAT.

180
00:09:23,019 --> 00:09:24,619
-HMM.

181
00:09:24,619 --> 00:09:28,153
-YOU WILL STAY HOME. GOT IT?

182
00:09:28,153 --> 00:09:31,119
BEING AS YOU ARE NOW
IS FOR THE BEST.

183
00:09:31,119 --> 00:09:34,186
-BUT RUE...
WANTS ME TO DANCE WITH HER.

184
00:09:34,186 --> 00:09:36,119
-FORGET ABOUT RUE.

185
00:09:36,119 --> 00:09:38,419
-I HAVE TO LET HER KNOW
I CAN'T GO.

186
00:09:38,419 --> 00:09:40,719
-ARE YOU DEFYING ME?

187
00:09:40,719 --> 00:09:42,119
-NO, BUT --

188
00:09:42,119 --> 00:09:43,953
-COME WITH ME.
-OH.

189
00:09:43,953 --> 00:09:46,719
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK, QUACK,
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK!

190
00:09:46,719 --> 00:09:49,719
-WHERE ARE WE GOING, FAKIR?

191
00:09:49,719 --> 00:09:53,486
FAKIR?
-NEVER MIND THAT.

192
00:09:53,486 --> 00:09:55,486
-QUACK, QUACK, QUACK,
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK, QUACK.

193
00:09:55,486 --> 00:09:56,953
QUACK?

194
00:10:01,986 --> 00:10:04,653
THE LIBRARY? QUACK!

195
00:10:04,653 --> 00:10:08,386
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK, QUACK,
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK -- AAH!

196
00:10:08,386 --> 00:10:10,386
<i>WOW!</i>

197
00:10:10,386 --> 00:10:14,653
<i>RUE!</i>

198
00:10:14,653 --> 00:10:18,386
<i>BUT FAKIR TOOK MYTHO AWAY.</i>

199
00:10:18,386 --> 00:10:22,019
<i>OH, ANYWAY, I HAVE TO</i>
<i>GO BACK TO BEING DUCK THE GIRL.</i>

200
00:10:22,019 --> 00:10:25,386
<i>WATER. WATER! QUACK!</i>

201
00:10:25,386 --> 00:10:26,886
[ DING! ]

202
00:10:26,886 --> 00:10:29,553
OHHHH.

203
00:10:31,986 --> 00:10:32,753
[ TWINKLE! ]

204
00:10:32,753 --> 00:10:34,486
[ GRUNTS ] YES!

205
00:10:34,486 --> 00:10:36,686
RUE!

206
00:10:36,686 --> 00:10:37,986
-DUCK.

207
00:10:37,986 --> 00:10:41,486
-S-SO, UH, YOU'RE
MEETING UP WITH MYTHO, RIGHT?

208
00:10:41,486 --> 00:10:43,986
-[ CHUCKLES ]
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

209
00:10:43,986 --> 00:10:46,486
-UH, WELL, UH, Y-YOU SEE,

210
00:10:46,486 --> 00:10:49,686
THE TRUTH IS I WAS KIND OF PUT
ON CLEANING DUTY AS PUNISHMENT,

211
00:10:49,686 --> 00:10:51,519
SO I WAS IN HERE CLEANING
NOT TOO LONG AGO,

212
00:10:51,519 --> 00:10:53,086
AND MYTHO WAS HERE, TOO,
AND HE SAID

213
00:10:53,086 --> 00:10:54,653
HE WAS GONNA PRACTICE
DANCING WITH YOU.

214
00:10:54,653 --> 00:10:56,553
WOW. IT'S TOTALLY WET OVER HERE.

215
00:10:56,553 --> 00:10:59,353
OF COURSE, I'M THE ONE
WHO MADE THE MESS. [ LAUGHS ]

216
00:10:59,353 --> 00:11:01,253
-SO, WHERE'S MYTHO?

217
00:11:01,253 --> 00:11:04,419
-OH. I THINK
HE STEPPED OUT FOR A BIT.

218
00:11:04,419 --> 00:11:06,386
-HMM. WHAT,
YOU DIDN'T GO CHASE HIM DOWN

219
00:11:06,386 --> 00:11:09,219
LIKE YOU DID THE OTHER DAY?
-OH. WELL...

220
00:11:09,219 --> 00:11:11,719
-AND THEN YOU SUDDENLY
DISAPPEARED FOR SOME REASON.

221
00:11:11,719 --> 00:11:13,719
-[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]
YEAH. SORRY.

222
00:11:13,719 --> 00:11:15,886
-IF YOU HAPPEN TO SEE MYTHO,

223
00:11:15,886 --> 00:11:18,553
PLEASE TELL HIM I'LL BE
GOING ON AHEAD TO THE SQUARE.

224
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:20,453
-OH. OKAY.

225
00:11:20,453 --> 00:11:21,919
HEY, RUE.

226
00:11:21,919 --> 00:11:24,119
MYTHO WILL COME AND FIND YOU.
I'M SURE HE WILL.

227
00:11:24,119 --> 00:11:27,453
YOU'RE LIKE A REAL PRINCESS,
AND YOU REALLY SUIT EACH OTHER,

228
00:11:27,453 --> 00:11:31,219
SO I'M SURE YOU'LL
GET THE GOLDEN APPLE, TOO.

229
00:11:31,219 --> 00:11:33,253
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

230
00:11:40,319 --> 00:11:43,819
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "MARCH"
FROM "THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

231
00:11:53,822 --> 00:11:56,989
<i>-I KNOW THEY</i>
<i>WENT IN THE LIBRARY FOR SURE,</i>

232
00:11:56,989 --> 00:11:58,589
<i>BUT, MM...</i>

233
00:12:01,989 --> 00:12:03,956
-STAY THERE AND BEHAVE YOURSELF.

234
00:12:03,956 --> 00:12:05,922
-WHY?
-PUNISHMENT.

235
00:12:05,922 --> 00:12:08,556
-I'M SORRY. DON'T BE MAD, FAKIR.

236
00:12:08,556 --> 00:12:10,422
I'LL DO AS YOU SAY.

237
00:12:10,422 --> 00:12:12,022
FAKIR, I --

238
00:12:14,122 --> 00:12:17,256
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!
PUNISHMENT?!

239
00:12:17,256 --> 00:12:20,389
WHY DO YOU ALWAYS
DO SUCH TERRIBLE THINGS?!

240
00:12:20,389 --> 00:12:23,222
AND YOU, MYTHO --
RUE'S WAITING FOR YOU!

241
00:12:23,222 --> 00:12:25,889
YOU FINALLY HAVE SOME SHARDS
OF YOUR HEART BACK NOW!

242
00:12:25,889 --> 00:12:29,222
YOU DON'T HAVE TO LISTEN
TO HIM ANYMO-- [ GASPS ]

243
00:12:29,222 --> 00:12:30,822
-SHARDS OF HIS HEART?

244
00:12:30,822 --> 00:12:32,222
YOUR NAME'S DUCK, RIGHT?

245
00:12:32,222 --> 00:12:33,656
JUST WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

246
00:12:33,656 --> 00:12:35,489
-N-NOTHING, REALLY.

247
00:12:35,489 --> 00:12:37,322
-COME TO THINK OF IT,
YOU ASKED ME ABOUT

248
00:12:37,322 --> 00:12:39,256
"THE PRINCE AND THE RAVEN"
THAT ONE TIME.

249
00:12:39,256 --> 00:12:41,722
-[ GASPS ]
-YOU KNOW, DON'T YOU?

250
00:12:41,722 --> 00:12:44,656
YOU KNOW THAT MYTHO IS ACTUALLY
A PRINCE FROM INSIDE A STORY.

251
00:12:44,656 --> 00:12:46,489
-[ GASPS ]

252
00:12:46,489 --> 00:12:49,522
-DID RUE TELL YOU?
<i>-RUE?</i>

253
00:12:49,522 --> 00:12:52,589
<i>RUE AND THIS PERSON</i>
<i>BOTH KNOW MYTHO'S SECRET?</i>

254
00:12:52,589 --> 00:12:54,256
AAH! UGH! UGH!

255
00:12:54,256 --> 00:12:56,522
-MYTHO HAS NO NEED OF A HEART.

256
00:12:56,522 --> 00:12:59,022
-HUH? HAS NO NEED OF A HEART?

257
00:12:59,022 --> 00:13:01,022
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
THERE'S NO WAY.

258
00:13:01,022 --> 00:13:03,289
-AND JUST WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

259
00:13:03,289 --> 00:13:05,256
I KNOW EVERYTHING ABOUT MYTHO.

260
00:13:05,256 --> 00:13:07,356
WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

261
00:13:07,356 --> 00:13:10,356
-WELL, SURE, I MAY NOT
KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT MYTHO,

262
00:13:10,356 --> 00:13:13,256
BUT IF HE'S MISSING HIS HEART,
HE WON'T KNOW HOW IT FEELS

263
00:13:13,256 --> 00:13:15,822
TO BE HAPPY OR BE IN LOVE,
EITHER.

264
00:13:15,822 --> 00:13:18,022
THAT'S WHY --
-FORGET IT.

265
00:13:18,022 --> 00:13:20,189
EVEN IF HE REGAINS
SHARDS OF HIS HEART,

266
00:13:20,189 --> 00:13:22,156
I'LL SEAL HIM AWAY.

267
00:13:22,156 --> 00:13:23,989
IF I SHUT HIM AWAY
IN THE DARKNESS,

268
00:13:23,989 --> 00:13:26,522
HE'LL BECOME NUMB
EVEN TO THE DARK.

269
00:13:26,522 --> 00:13:30,489
NUMB TO ALL SENSATION,
HE'LL STOP FEELING ALL TOGETHER.

270
00:13:30,489 --> 00:13:34,022
-THAT'S JUST --
THAT'S JUST TERRIBLE OF YOU!

271
00:13:34,022 --> 00:13:35,456
[ CRYING ]

272
00:13:35,456 --> 00:13:38,389
-DON'T LET YOUR IGNORANCE
CARRY YOU AWAY.

273
00:13:41,356 --> 00:13:45,089
<i>-ACTING SO HIGH AND MIGHTY,</i>
<i>LIKE HE KNOWS EVERYTHING.</i>

274
00:13:45,089 --> 00:13:48,522
<i>WHEN I GAVE MYTHO BACK HIS</i>
<i>HEART SHARDS, HE THANKED ME.</i>

275
00:13:48,522 --> 00:13:50,389
<i>HE DID!</i>

276
00:13:53,989 --> 00:13:55,889
-[ LAUGHS ]

277
00:13:55,889 --> 00:13:57,756
ARE YOU AFRAID OF THE DARK?

278
00:13:59,789 --> 00:14:01,856
YOU'LL BE OKAY.

279
00:14:01,856 --> 00:14:04,389
<i>-BUT IT'S TRUE.</i>

280
00:14:04,389 --> 00:14:08,089
<i>I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING --</i>
<i>NOT WHEN IT COMES TO MYTHO.</i>

281
00:14:08,089 --> 00:14:11,856
AM I STICKING MY NOSE
WHERE IT DOESN'T BELONG?

282
00:14:11,856 --> 00:14:14,389
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

283
00:14:17,522 --> 00:14:18,589
MISS EDEL!

284
00:14:18,589 --> 00:14:21,622
-THE FLAME CAN ILLUMINATE
THE DARKNESS,

285
00:14:21,622 --> 00:14:25,189
BUT WITHOUT THE DARKNESS,
ITS GLOW CANNOT BE SEEN.

286
00:14:25,189 --> 00:14:27,522
ARE YOU AFRAID OF THE DARK?
-[ GASPS ]

287
00:14:27,522 --> 00:14:30,289
-I SEE YOU'RE
IN THE DARKNESS OF UNCERTAINTY.

288
00:14:30,289 --> 00:14:32,656
BUT IF YOU WISH TO SHINE
FOR SOMEONE,

289
00:14:32,656 --> 00:14:35,522
YOU MUST NOT FEAR THE DARKNESS.

290
00:14:35,522 --> 00:14:36,922
-I SEE.

291
00:14:36,922 --> 00:14:40,156
YOU MEAN I SHOULDN'T FEAR
WHAT I DON'T UNDERSTAND, RIGHT?

292
00:14:40,156 --> 00:14:41,656
-HMM.

293
00:14:41,656 --> 00:14:44,722
A PATH IS OPEN TO YOU.

294
00:14:47,122 --> 00:14:49,622
<i>-WHAT? HE'S NOT HERE?</i>

295
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:51,522
<i>MYTHO, WHERE DID YOU GO?!</i>

296
00:14:51,522 --> 00:14:53,756
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK, QUACK,
QUACK!

297
00:14:53,756 --> 00:14:55,956
AAAAAAAAAAAAH!

298
00:14:55,956 --> 00:14:57,322
OHH! QUACK!

299
00:14:57,322 --> 00:14:58,756
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK!

300
00:14:58,756 --> 00:15:00,422
[ GRUNTS ]
QUACK! QUACK!

301
00:15:00,422 --> 00:15:01,956
AAH!

302
00:15:01,956 --> 00:15:03,922
[ DRIP! TWINKLE! ]

303
00:15:06,456 --> 00:15:07,922
[ TWINKLE! ]

304
00:15:07,922 --> 00:15:09,222
[ GASPS ]

305
00:15:09,222 --> 00:15:10,456
OHH.

306
00:15:10,456 --> 00:15:12,456
HUH?

307
00:15:12,456 --> 00:15:15,689
THIS IS WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE
UNDER THE LIBRARY?

308
00:15:15,689 --> 00:15:16,956
-[ LAUGHING ]
-[ GASPS ]

309
00:15:16,956 --> 00:15:19,189
OH, IT'S A HEART SHARD.

310
00:15:19,189 --> 00:15:21,522
-[ LAUGHING CONTINUES ]

311
00:15:21,522 --> 00:15:24,256
-WHO'S THERE? MYTHO?

312
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:25,556
ARE YOU THERE?

313
00:15:25,556 --> 00:15:29,089
-I'M JUST A LITTLE THING,
BUT I FLOOD THE ENTIRE ROOM.

314
00:15:29,089 --> 00:15:31,122
-WHAT AM I?
-A RIDDLE?

315
00:15:31,122 --> 00:15:32,222
HMM?
-[ LAUGHING ]

316
00:15:32,222 --> 00:15:33,322
-[ GASPS ]

317
00:15:33,322 --> 00:15:34,989
-[ LAUGHING CONTINUES ]

318
00:15:34,989 --> 00:15:37,222
-IT'S COMING
FROM THE OTHER SIDE.

319
00:15:37,222 --> 00:15:41,122
I MUSTN'T FEAR THE DARKNESS.

320
00:15:41,122 --> 00:15:44,489
OKAY, JUST A LITTLE THING
THAT FLOODS THE ENTIRE ROOM.

321
00:15:44,489 --> 00:15:46,589
OH, A SNEEZE!
-TOO BAD.

322
00:15:46,589 --> 00:15:49,989
I'M A WHITE SNAKE
THAT SWALLOWS THE SEA.

323
00:15:49,989 --> 00:15:51,789
WHAT AM I?

324
00:15:51,789 --> 00:15:54,789
-UM, A WHITE PAINTBRUSH
WITH RED PAINT ON IT?

325
00:15:54,789 --> 00:15:57,189
-[ LAUGHS ] TOO BAD.

326
00:15:57,189 --> 00:15:59,222
HERE'S THE LAST ONE.

327
00:15:59,222 --> 00:16:04,122
I BECOME SHORTER
THE LONGER I STAND. WHAT AM I?

328
00:16:04,122 --> 00:16:08,122
-SO, YOU'RE, LIKE,
A FLOWER, RIGHT?

329
00:16:08,122 --> 00:16:10,522
-TOO BAD.
BUT CONGRATULATIONS.

330
00:16:10,522 --> 00:16:12,856
THE PERSON YOU'RE LOOKING FOR
IS HERE.

331
00:16:12,856 --> 00:16:15,189
-WHAT? MYTHO?
GIVE HIM BACK!

332
00:16:15,189 --> 00:16:17,122
-NO.
-AAH!

333
00:16:17,122 --> 00:16:19,322
-YOU ALSO ARE TO STAY HERE.

334
00:16:19,322 --> 00:16:22,922
-I CAN'T DO THAT!
-YOU'LL BE FINE. I'M HERE.

335
00:16:22,922 --> 00:16:24,822
-WHO...ARE YOU?

336
00:16:24,822 --> 00:16:26,589
-OH, DEAR. OH, DEAR.

337
00:16:26,589 --> 00:16:30,522
ARE YOU TO BECOME A PRISONER OF
THE DARKNESS, NOW AND FOREVER,

338
00:16:30,522 --> 00:16:34,856
OR WILL YOU BE ABLE TO REKINDLE
YOUR RADIANCE, PRINCESS TUTU?

339
00:16:34,856 --> 00:16:38,156
[ TWINKLE! ]

340
00:16:43,322 --> 00:16:45,622
[ TWINKLE! ]

341
00:16:50,989 --> 00:16:53,489
-ARE YOU THERE?

342
00:16:53,489 --> 00:16:55,922
-WHO ARE YOU?

343
00:16:55,922 --> 00:16:58,122
-I AM PRINCESS TUTU.

344
00:16:58,122 --> 00:17:01,822
-YOU'RE WONDERFUL.
PLEASE STAY AND DANCE.

345
00:17:01,822 --> 00:17:05,089
I'LL ILLUMINATE YOU
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

346
00:17:05,089 --> 00:17:07,222
-ILLUMINATE ME?

347
00:17:07,222 --> 00:17:08,489
-THAT'S RIGHT.
-SO, THAT'S IT --

348
00:17:08,489 --> 00:17:10,689
THE LITTLE THING THAT FLOODS
THE ENTIRE ROOM

349
00:17:10,689 --> 00:17:12,356
IS THE LIGHT OF A LAMP, THEN.

350
00:17:12,356 --> 00:17:15,722
AND THE WHITE SNAKE WITH THE RED
HEAD THAT SWALLOWS THE SEA

351
00:17:15,722 --> 00:17:19,222
AND BECOMES SHORTER THE LONGER
IT STANDS IS THE LAMP'S WICK.

352
00:17:19,222 --> 00:17:21,689
YOU'RE A LAMP.
AM I RIGHT?

353
00:17:21,689 --> 00:17:24,189
-YOU ARE CORRECT.

354
00:17:26,722 --> 00:17:28,756
-HMM.

355
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:31,222
NOW, PLEASE, GIVE BACK MYTHO
AND HIS HEART.

356
00:17:31,222 --> 00:17:32,989
-NO.

357
00:17:34,022 --> 00:17:36,589
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

358
00:17:43,722 --> 00:17:45,256
-IDIOT.

359
00:17:49,071 --> 00:17:50,571
-PLEASE DANCE WITH ME.

360
00:17:50,571 --> 00:17:52,571
-DANCE WITH YOU?

361
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:54,104
-YES.

362
00:17:54,104 --> 00:17:56,304
[ GASPS ]

363
00:17:56,304 --> 00:17:57,604
-YOU DANCE.

364
00:17:57,604 --> 00:17:59,971
I WILL LIGHT YOUR STEPS.

365
00:17:59,971 --> 00:18:01,038
-MM.

366
00:18:10,671 --> 00:18:13,638
[ TWINKLE! TWINKLE! TWINKLE! ]

367
00:18:18,804 --> 00:18:21,871
YOUR LIGHT
IS SO WARM AND GENTLE.

368
00:18:21,871 --> 00:18:23,904
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

369
00:18:23,904 --> 00:18:25,971
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

370
00:18:25,971 --> 00:18:28,171
-MY ONE WISH -- MY ONLY WISH --

371
00:18:28,171 --> 00:18:30,771
IS TO KEEP ON SHINING
FOR SOMEONE.

372
00:18:30,771 --> 00:18:33,738
I WANT TO ENVELOP THEM TENDERLY
IN WARM LIGHT.

373
00:18:33,738 --> 00:18:35,438
-WANTING TO SHINE FOR SOMEONE?

374
00:18:35,438 --> 00:18:39,038
-THAT WAS ALL.
I DIDN'T WANT ANYTHING ELSE.

375
00:18:39,038 --> 00:18:42,938
AND YET SOMEWHERE ALONG THE WAY,
I HAD SUDDENLY BECOME FORGOTTEN.

376
00:18:42,938 --> 00:18:45,104
THE PEOPLE
WHO ARE PRECIOUS TO ME

377
00:18:45,104 --> 00:18:47,704
FORGOT ABOUT ME
AND THE LIGHT I GAVE THEM.

378
00:18:47,704 --> 00:18:51,804
NO, THEY MUST NOT HAVE NEEDED ME
FROM THE BEGINNING.

379
00:18:51,804 --> 00:18:53,138
-THAT CAN'T BE TRUE.

380
00:18:53,138 --> 00:18:55,538
-I THOUGHT
THEY ENJOYED MY PRESENCE,

381
00:18:55,538 --> 00:18:57,504
BUT THAT WAS ONLY
WHEN I BELIEVED.

382
00:18:57,504 --> 00:18:59,938
-I'M SURE THAT'S NOT TRUE.

383
00:18:59,938 --> 00:19:03,971
-BUT RIGHT NOW, THERE IS SOMEONE
WHO WANTS MY LIGHT.

384
00:19:05,171 --> 00:19:07,838
-[ GASPS ] MYTHO.

385
00:19:09,638 --> 00:19:12,871
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT --
TO SHUT HIM AWAY?

386
00:19:12,871 --> 00:19:14,838
-YES.

387
00:19:16,038 --> 00:19:19,371
I WILL STAY HERE
AND ILLUMINATE HIM FOR ALL TIME.

388
00:19:19,371 --> 00:19:21,404
-PLEASE,
REMEMBER WHAT IT WAS LIKE

389
00:19:21,404 --> 00:19:24,504
TO HAVE YOUR WARM LIGHT SHINE
ON THE PEOPLE YOU LOVE.

390
00:19:28,404 --> 00:19:30,071
-I HAVEN'T FORGOTTEN.

391
00:19:30,071 --> 00:19:33,904
-THEN YOU SHOULD KNOW
FORCING YOUR WARMTH ON PEOPLE

392
00:19:33,904 --> 00:19:36,671
WON'T BRING JOY TO ANYONE.

393
00:19:36,671 --> 00:19:40,038
I LOVE THE SOFT AND TENDER GLOW
OF YOUR WARM LIGHT.

394
00:19:40,038 --> 00:19:43,271
I BELIEVE THAT THE PEOPLE
WHO ARE PRECIOUS TO YOU

395
00:19:43,271 --> 00:19:47,971
WERE VERY HAPPY TO HAVE YOU
ENVELOP THEM WITH THAT GLOW.

396
00:19:47,971 --> 00:19:50,504
IT'S SAD
THAT THEY NO LONGER NEED YOU,

397
00:19:50,504 --> 00:19:53,138
BUT IT'S SOMETHING
THAT CAN'T BE HELPED,

398
00:19:53,138 --> 00:19:56,671
BECAUSE IT ISN'T SOMETHING
THAT YOU CAN FORCE ON PEOPLE.

399
00:19:58,304 --> 00:20:01,371
IF YOU WANT WHAT IS BEST
FOR MYTHO,

400
00:20:01,371 --> 00:20:02,904
RETURN HIS HEART.

401
00:20:02,904 --> 00:20:04,704
THAT WILL BRING HIM HAPPINESS.

402
00:20:04,704 --> 00:20:05,838
-WILL IT?

403
00:20:05,838 --> 00:20:08,671
-IT'S WHAT I BELIEVE.

404
00:20:11,571 --> 00:20:18,038
-PRINCESS TUTU, I WANT TO
CONTINUE ILLUMINATING YOU.

405
00:20:23,004 --> 00:20:26,704
-I AM THE FEELING OF AFFECTION
SHATTERED AND FORGOTTEN.

406
00:20:26,704 --> 00:20:29,171
-THE FEELING OF AFFECTION.

407
00:20:29,171 --> 00:20:30,704
[ TWINKLE! TWINKLE! ]

408
00:20:30,704 --> 00:20:34,671
-OH.
RETURN TO MYTHO NOW.

409
00:20:35,938 --> 00:20:39,004
[ TWINKLE! ]

410
00:20:39,004 --> 00:20:41,204
-[ GRUNTS SOFTLY ]

411
00:20:41,204 --> 00:20:43,071
-[ GASPS ]

412
00:20:43,071 --> 00:20:44,704
MYTHO.

413
00:20:44,704 --> 00:20:45,771
-PRINCESS TUTU.

414
00:20:45,771 --> 00:20:47,204
-YOU SHOULD HURRY NOW.

415
00:20:47,204 --> 00:20:48,204
-HUH?

416
00:20:48,204 --> 00:20:51,204
-SOMEONE IS WAITING FOR YOU.

417
00:20:51,204 --> 00:20:53,671
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

418
00:20:56,204 --> 00:20:57,738
-HMPH.

419
00:20:57,738 --> 00:21:00,238
I WAS SUCH A FOOL
FOR BELIEVING WHAT DUCK SAID.

420
00:21:01,404 --> 00:21:03,704
[ GASPS ]
MYTHO.

421
00:21:05,638 --> 00:21:07,738
THE FIRE FESTIVAL ENDED
LONG AGO.

422
00:21:07,738 --> 00:21:09,704
-SORRY.

423
00:21:09,704 --> 00:21:12,604
-MYTHO, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
MYTHO?

424
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:14,638
[ SAINT-SAENS' "AQUARIUM"
FROM "CARNIVAL OF
THE ANIMALS" PLAYS ]

425
00:21:14,638 --> 00:21:17,004
STOP IT.
YOU'RE ACTING STRANGE.

426
00:21:18,771 --> 00:21:20,238
-THIS IS HOW IT SHOULD BE.

427
00:21:20,238 --> 00:21:21,838
-[ LAUGHS ]

428
00:21:21,838 --> 00:21:23,938
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

429
00:21:28,238 --> 00:21:29,271
[ GASPS ]

430
00:21:30,938 --> 00:21:32,838
[ GASPS ]

431
00:21:35,571 --> 00:21:38,771
FOR SUCH KINDNESS TO BE
IN YOUR EYES, IT'S...

432
00:21:38,771 --> 00:21:40,838
-RUE.

433
00:21:40,838 --> 00:21:43,538
-[ GASPS ]

434
00:21:43,538 --> 00:21:46,338
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

435
00:21:50,604 --> 00:21:51,938
-[ GASPS ]

436
00:21:51,938 --> 00:21:53,104
OH, RUE.

437
00:21:53,104 --> 00:21:56,038
-THE PRINCE REGAINED
THE FEELING OF HAPPINESS,

438
00:21:56,038 --> 00:21:58,738
BUT HAS IT ILLUMINATED
DUCK'S UNHAPPINESS?

439
00:21:58,738 --> 00:22:00,971
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

440
00:22:04,504 --> 00:22:06,804
[ SLOW MUSIC PLAYING ]

441
00:22:17,604 --> 00:22:20,938
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

442
00:23:34,438 --> 00:23:35,538
-LOVE?!

443
00:23:35,538 --> 00:23:38,571
IT'S REALLY NOT ANYTHING
LIKE THAT WITH ME!

444
00:23:38,571 --> 00:23:39,571
-I'M SURE.

445
00:23:39,571 --> 00:23:40,938
SHE'S PURSUING
A WONDERFUL DREAM,

446
00:23:40,938 --> 00:23:43,338
AND CHANCES ARE
SHE'S ALSO IN LOVE.

447
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:45,404
-YOU'LL ALWAYS WAKE UP
FROM A DREAM.

448
00:23:45,404 --> 00:23:46,604
-NO.
-YOU MUST WAKE UP.

449
00:23:46,604 --> 00:23:48,371
-WHAT'S THIS?
YOU'RE TREMBLING.

450
00:23:48,371 --> 00:23:50,438
-I'M AFRAID OF PRINCESS TUTU.

451
00:23:50,438 --> 00:23:52,638
-I JUST WANTED MYTHO TO SMILE.

452
00:23:52,638 --> 00:23:54,204
THAT'S ALL I WANTED.

453
00:23:54,204 --> 00:23:57,438
HAVE I JUST DONE
SOMETHING TERRIBLE TO MYTHO?

454
00:23:57,438 --> 00:24:00,904
-ALL WHO LOVE STORIES,
GATHER 'ROUND.

455
00:24:00,904 --> 00:24:02,438
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

